'''Scott Smith''' (born October 19, 1981 in [[Ft. Lauderdale, Florida]]) is an American [[figure skating|figure skater]]. He was the 1999 US Junior National Champion and 2003 national pewter medalist.
==Biography== Smith represents the [[Skating Club of Boston]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Scott Smith, ISU Biography | url = http://www.isufs.org/bios/isufs00003323.htm}}</ref>
At the 2006 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]], he was the only competitor to land a clean quadruple jump.
Smith trained, for a time, at the [[University of Delaware Figure Skating Club]] in [[Newark, Delaware]], then moved to the Skating Club of Boston, and was coached by [[Mark Mitchell (American figure skater)|Mark Mitchell]] and [[Peter Johansson (figure skater)|Peter Johansson]]. His programs have been choreographed by Jamie Isley, [[Lori Nichol]] and [[Nikolai Morozov (figure skater)|Nikolai Morozov]]. Before the [[2008 U.S. Figure Skating Championships]], he changed coaches again, this time to work with Stephanie Grosscup in Salt Lake City.<ref>[http://web.icenetwork.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20080127&content_id=43127&vkey=ice_news icenetwork.com: News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
He withdrew from the 2009 U.S. Figure Skating Championships due to muscle spasms in his back, just before he was to skate his short program.<ref>{{cite news | title = Journal | publisher = Scott Smith Online | date = 2/24/2009 | url = http://www.figureskatersonline.com/scottsmith/journal.html | accessdate = 5/9/2009}}</ref>
